description.text: this message file contains message for [name] package

msg.text: Secondary clock $$s has loads or driver cross to other module, the skew cannot be guaranteed in the assembly flow.
Clock net $$s uses delayed mode and will be routed using generic routing interconnect; this may cause excessive delay or skew.

A remote spine is used for the normal clock net $$s because the spine local to the driver is occupied by another net or not able to route to all/most loads through dedicated clock routing resource. This net may suffer from excessive delay or skew. You may need to check your preference file to see if more than one clock net is driven from the same block of four PIO cells which share a clock spine.
Unable to route net $$s (PLL to ECLKSYN) with dedicated resource which may cause excessive.
Unable to route net $$s (PIO to DLL_CLKI / PLL_CLKI) with dedicated routing resource, and may suffer from excessive delay using general routing.\n
There is no primary Hspine available for signal $$s.

The driver of primary clock net $$s is not placed on one of the dedicated sites for primary clocks. This primary clock will be routed to a H-spine through general routing resource and may suffer from excessive delay or skew.
There is no single load routed for secondary clock signal $$s.
Some loads of pclk net $$s have to be routed use general routing due to DCS/DCC site occupied by comp $$s.
No branch nodes have been found for the primary clock signal $$s. The signal will be routed with other routing resources.\n
The driver of edge clock net $$s is not placed on one of the dedicated sites. This edge clock will be routed through general routing resource and may suffer from excessive delay or skew.
There is no HSBX available for secondary clock signal $$s.

The driver of secondary clock net $$s is not placed on one of the PIO sites dedicated for secondary clocks. This secondary clock will be routed through general routing resource and may suffer from excessive delay or skew.

The driver of primary clock net $$s is not placed on one of the PIO sites dedicated for primary clocks. This primary clock will be routed to a H-spine through general routing resource and may suffer from excessive delay or skew.
Unable to route net (PIO to DLL_CLKI / PLL_CLKI) with dedicated resource for net $$s.\n
